'''''Star Wars'' 51''' is the fifty-first issue in the [[Star Wars (1977)|''Marvel Star Wars'']] series of comics.

==Plot summary==
[[General/Legends|General]] [[Carlist Rieekan/Legends|Rieekan]] receives word from [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] spies that the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] is constructing a new superweapon known as the [[Tarkin (superweapon)|''Tarkin'']]. Realizing the danger the new weapon poses, Rieekan sends for the group of Rebels who survived the original [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]], and the [[Droid/Legends|droids]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]]. The three Rebels and two droids are sent to the planet [[Hockaleg]] in the [[Patriim system/Legends|Patriim system]] in order to infiltrate an Imperial construction crew and make their way on board the ''Tarkin''. However, [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] observes as the Rebels arrive in the giant weapon, and sets events in motion to capture his long sought after adversary, Luke Skywalker. But little does the Dark Lord know that some of his own men are secretly plotting against him due to his vicious punishments imposed against their fellow Imperial officers.

==Development==
[[David Michelinie]] and [[Walter Simonson|Walt Simonson]] begin their regular run on the title with this issue. The names of Walt Simonson, [[Tom Palmer]] (inker), and [[Louise Simonson|Louise Jones]] (editor) can be seen in the close-up of the blueprints to the ''Tarkin'' during the briefing-room scene.

==Continuity==
Creatures called [[Gundark/Legends|gundarks]] make their first appearance in the [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]], but they are very different from their later Expanded Universe and canonical forms. The creatures in this issue were [[Retroactive continuity|retconned]] to be [[long-necked gundark]]s.

In this issue, Luke has and uses a [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]], despite having lost his in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']]. While this is also true of issues [[Star Wars (1977) 45|45]] and [[Star Wars (1977) 49|49]] of this series, the art in those issues did not clearly show the shape of the hilt. In this issue, however, the hilt seems to be that of [[Anakin Skywalker's second lightsaber/Legends|his first lightsaber]], the one lost in [[Star Wars (1977) 44|issue 44]] (corresponding to the events of ''The Empire Strikes Back'').

